"At this stage, it is rarely possible to use cultures. # Treating Cases\nLong treatments (12-18 months) are no longer recommended. 102 Short treatments currently constitute the appropriate therapy. The patient's sputum becomes negative quickly (within two or three weeks), thereby also reducing the risk of transmission in the population. Under these circumstances, the treatment of patients with positive sputum can be considered as a form of primary prevention for the entire population. The institution of a TB treatment program is subject to certain rules:\n-Treatment is provided for subjects with positive sputum. -The logistical arrangements must insure that patients are under care for the entire period required for their treatment."